      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: tolerate EPERM in session write-lock on Windows",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- On Windows, `fs.open(path, \"wx\")` can throw `EPERM` instead of `EEXIST` when another process holds the lock file open (Windows mandatory file locking). This causes an unhandled promise rejection crash in `acquireSessionWriteLock`.\n- Treat `EPERM` the same as `EEXIST` so the lock acquisition retries instead of crashing.\n- Added test for EPERM retry behavior.\n\n## Context\n\nReported by @yangzhengkun — Windows users hit this crash:\n\n```\nUnhandled promise rejection: Error: EPERM: operation not permitted, open '...\\sessions.json.lock'\n    at acquireSessionWriteLock (session-write-lock-*.js)\n```\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Existing `session-write-lock.test.ts` tests pass (20/20)\n- [x] New test: `retries on EPERM during lock acquisition (Windows mandatory locking)` — mocks `fs.open` to throw EPERM twice, verifies lock is acquired on retry",
